<dl id="sa0021j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0021j">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../FF/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0021j"> 021(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> So they put on / the kettle and made tea and if they don&apos;t live / happy that you and I may, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="sa0021j"><li>FW 229.29 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kb/lexkb.htm#sa0021j">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kb/l39kb.htm#sa0021j">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#sa0021j">MS BL 47477-60</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:055 <a name="kbd1y" href="../../FF/fdra/kda.htm#kbd1y">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kb/kbd1.htm#sa0021j">Draft: II.1&sect;2.1</a>+</li> </ul> <ul class="list-inline" id="sa0021j"></li><li>FW 332.02-4 </li><li><a href="../../flex/mb/lexmb.htm#sa0021j">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/mb/l39mb.htm#sa0021j">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#sa0021j">MS Missing</ms> </li><li>JJA not reproduced <a name="mbd6" href="../../FF/fdra/mda.htm#mbd6">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/mb/mbd6.htm#sa0021j">Draft: II.3&sect;2.6</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Burton writes of formulaic endings of the Stories. A common ending of fairy-tales is &ldquo;<mark>So they put on the kettle and made tea. If they don&apos;t live happy ever after that you and I may</mark>&rdquo;]</font>. <small> Richard Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo; in <a name="RB01" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RB01"><cite title="source">1000 Nights and 1 Night</cite></a> (Denver, 1919) x.</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The words &lsquo;So they put on&rsquo; are not crossed through. Second use was entered in September 1938, and possibly does not derive from this notebook. </mm> </dd></dl>
